                <div class="section-label"><span class="icon">🎨</span> Art & Craft</div>
                <h2>Madhubani Art – The Soul of Mithila</h2>
                <p>
                    Madhubani art, also known as Mithila painting, is a traditional
                    folk art form that originated in the Mithila region. It is
                    characterized by intricate geometric patterns, vibrant natural dyes,
                    and depictions of mythology, nature, and daily life.
                </p>
                <p>
                    Traditionally painted by women on walls and floors during festivals
                    and ceremonies, Madhubani art has now gained global recognition.
                    The art form uses natural pigments derived from plants, minerals,
                    and even cow dung, making it both sustainable and deeply connected
                    to the land.
                </p>
                <div style="margin-top:var(--space-lg);">
                    <a href="/madhubani-art" class="btn btn-primary">Explore Madhubani Art →</a>
                </div>
