                <div class="section-label"><span class="icon">🎵</span> Music & Dance</div>
                <h2>Melodies and Movements of Mithila</h2>
                <p>
                    Maithili music is deeply rooted in the region's folk traditions.
                    From the devotional <strong>bhajans</strong> sung in temples to the
                    lively <strong>sama</strong> and <strong>dhunuchi</strong> dances
                    performed during festivals, music and dance are integral to Mithila's
                    cultural identity.
                </p>
                <p>
                    The <strong>Maithili folk dance</strong> forms are diverse — each
                    with its own rhythm and story. The <strong>Jhijhiya</strong> dance,
                    performed during the rainy season, and the <strong>Domkach</strong>
                    dance, a wedding tradition, are just a few examples of the region's
                    rich performing arts heritage.
                </p>
                <div style="margin-top:var(--space-lg);">
                    <a href="/music" class="btn btn-primary">Explore Music →</a>
                    <a href="/dance" class="btn btn-outline" style="margin-left:var(--space-sm);">Explore Dance →</a>
                </div>
