                <h2>Timeless Traditions</h2>
                <p>
                    Mithila's traditions are a reflection of its deep spiritual and
                    cultural roots. From the sacred <strong>Vivah Panchami</strong>
                    festival celebrating the marriage of Lord Rama and Sita, to the
                    vibrant <strong>Chhath Puja</strong> dedicated to the Sun God —
                    every tradition in Mithila tells a story of faith and community.
                </p>
                <p>
                    The region is also known for its unique customs around marriage,
                    childbirth, and harvest. These traditions are often accompanied by
                    special rituals, songs, and art forms that have been preserved
                    for centuries.
                </p>
