                    Maithili is not just a language — it is the soul of Mithila.
                    One of the 22 official languages of India, Maithili has a rich
                    literary tradition that spans over a millennium. From the poetry of
                    <strong>Vidyapati</strong> to contemporary Maithili literature,
                    the language has been a vehicle for expressing love, devotion,
                    and social commentary.
                </p>
                <p>
                    The preservation and promotion of Maithili is a key part of
                    Mithila's cultural renaissance. Today, the language is taught in
                    schools, used in media, and celebrated in literary festivals
                    across the region.
